  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For two systems (Q 2237+0305 and HE 0435-1223), a forward modeling of the observed deformation has been performed (cf.",
    "Sect. 3.5.3), strongly favouring a keplerian disc geometry (Braibant et al. 2016; Hutsemekers et al. 2019; Hutsemékers and Sluse 2021).",
    "A half-light radius r 1/2 (Hβ) = 47 ± 19 lt-days has been derived for Q 2237+0305, about an order of magnitude below the expectation from R BLR -L relation derived from reverberation mapping (Grier et al. 2017).",
    "Hutsemékers and Sluse (2021) have proposed that this could be related to the high accretion rate estimated for that system.",
    "The comparison of line deformations based on data obtained at the same epoch (or pairs of data accounting for the time delay) provide further insights on the existence of a common BLR structure for various atomic species."
  ],
